================================================================================
Borrowed test fixture content (Apache-2.0 source)
================================================================================

The repository includes test fixtures borrowed verbatim from the upstream
Turnkey open-source repositories. Each borrowed fixture is bundled under
tests/Fixtures/ and codex-crypto-reviews/upstream-snapshots/ together with
its source URL and the git tag SHA from which the bytes were copied. The
following borrowings are made under the Apache-2.0 license:

  - codex-crypto-reviews/upstream-snapshots/turnkey-{crypto-2.8.8,
      http-3.16.0, api-key-stamper-0.5.0, encoding-0.6.0}/
    Source: https://github.com/tkhq/sdk (Apache-2.0)
    Pinned git tag SHAs: see codex-crypto-reviews/turnkey-source-pins.md

  - tests/Fixtures/proofs/upstream-proof-tests-fixture.json
    Extracted from codex-crypto-reviews/upstream-snapshots/turnkey-crypto-2.8.8/
      ts-source/__tests__/proof-tests.ts
    Source: https://github.com/tkhq/sdk (Apache-2.0)

The hex constants `mockSenderPrivateKey`, `mockPrivateKey`,
`mockCredentialBundle`, the BIP-39 mnemonic ("leaf lady until indicate
praise final route toast cake minimum insect unknown"), and the PEM key
material used in tests/CryptoTests.cs and tests/ApiKeyStamperTests.cs are
copied verbatim from upstream tkhq/sdk and tkhq/swift-sdk / tkhq/dart-sdk
fixtures; their source URLs are recorded in the relevant Codex review
documents under codex-crypto-reviews/.
